        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down Bromley Kent</placeName>
                    <date>March 4<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Huxley</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>You poor Londoners I daresay never see the Gardeners’ Chronicle so I write to say that in to days number, there appears the following.</p> 
<figure type="diagram"> 
<p>“We borrow from the Times the following brilliant notice of the work &amp;c &amp;c”</p> </figure> 
<p>Then comes your whole Article—<ref target="#foot.f2"/> I never knew G. Ch. do such a thing before    see you best of “general agents” what capital service you have done in the good cause of removing prejudice &amp;c.</p>
<p>Yours Most sincerely | C. Darwin</p>
<p>By the way, a fortnight ago Harvey attacked my book in rather weak article, &amp; Hooker made really admirable rejoinder in last week’s number.—<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p> 
                </div>
            </div>
                <div type="tnotes">
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n1">2.1 I never … before] <hi rend="italic">added</hi></note>
                </div>

            
        </div>

        

        

